{"TopicId":181040,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Align \u0026#039;target\u0026#039; with \u0026#039;prograde\u0026#039;","CreatedByName":"WillWam","CreatedById":193139,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-01T16:51:28Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"WillWam","CreatedById":193139,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-01T16:51:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow can I \u003Cu\u003Equickly\u003C/u\u003E align \u0027target\u0027 with \u0027prograde\u0027 on the navball\u00A0(I\u0027m learning how to dock)? I keep flying past my target because my prograde isn\u0027t lined up all the way with my target.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-01-01T16:57:44Z\u0022 title=\u002201/01/2019 04:57  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 1, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by WillWam\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-01T17:11:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI usually use the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E translation controls (JKLI).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"WillWam","CreatedById":193139,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-01T17:25:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223514452\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181040\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221546362665\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022156657\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HebaruSan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 minutes ago, HebaruSan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI usually use the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E translation controls (JKLI).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkay, so what I\u0027ve been doing is using \u0027target\u0027 on the navball. Do I just freehand it? Do I keep \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E on?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-01T17:44:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223514462\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181040\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221546363540\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022193139\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022WillWam\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 minutes ago, WillWam said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkay, so what I\u0027ve been doing is using \u0027target\u0027 on the navball. Do I just freehand it? Do I keep \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E on?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, the nav ball should be in target mode. When you\u0027re first learning, turn on both \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E and add some extra monopropellant fuel to your craft so you don\u0027t run out while practicing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe translation controls (IJKL) allow you to move the prograde vector around. Assuming that you are facing prograde, I/K will move it up and down, J/L will move it left and right. You can use this to place it over the target marker.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-01-01T17:45:33Z\u0022 title=\u002201/01/2019 05:45  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 1, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by HebaruSan\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"WillWam","CreatedById":193139,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-01T17:46:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223514468\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181040\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221546364698\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022156657\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HebaruSan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, HebaruSan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, the nav ball should be in target mode. When you\u0027re first learning, turn on both \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E and add some extra monopropellant fuel to your craft so you don\u0027t run out while practicing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe translation controls (IJKL) allow you to move the prograde vector around. Assuming that you are facing prograde, I/K will move it up and down, J/L will move it left and right. You can use this to place it over the target marker.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGot it! Also, I just turn on infinite fuel \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-01T20:25:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, you don\u0027t really have to quickly align prograde with the target, exactly. You burn a couple times to get it close, certainly -- while you are inbound. Then you align\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003Eretrograde.\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0If you burn to 0.0m/s retrograde in target mode, that means you are stopped relative to your target. So as you are drifting past your target, you do that burn. Now you are stopped. Now you point straight at the target and give it a little juice. You will probably still miss the second time, unless you were less than 30 meters apart, or unless you use \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E to correct small errors in your aim. But once you stop relative to your target, you\u0027ve got all the time in the world to do your alignment.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snark","CreatedById":125662,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-01T22:04:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/193139-willwam/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022193139\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/193139-willwam/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@WillWam\u003C/a\u003E,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you\u0027re asking about the process of getting things lined up for docking, here\u0027s an \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/189763-illustrated-guide-to-docking/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Eillustrated docking tutorial\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E I put together a while back, that you may find helpful.\u00A0 \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"WillWam","CreatedById":193139,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-02T00:28:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223514593\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181040\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221546380268\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022125662\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Snark\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Snark said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/193139-willwam/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022193139\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/193139-willwam/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@WillWam\u003C/a\u003E,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you\u0027re asking about the process of getting things lined up for docking, here\u0027s an \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://web.archive.org/web/20151126132127/http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/entries/3770-Illustrated-guide-to-docking\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Eillustrated docking tutorial\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E I put together a while back, that you may find helpful.\u00A0 \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cu\u003EExtremely\u003C/u\u003E\u00A0helpful. Please consider reposting that on the current forum software! I didn\u0027t know about the\u00A0fine-control mode! I am currently trying this right now in KSP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GoatRider","CreatedById":103681,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-02T01:05:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne trick that I use when docking two ships that are both pilotable is align to target from both sides- that is, if you have a station and a ship, use the bracket keys to switch to the station, control from the desired docking port, set the docking port as the target, and align to it using the nav ball.\u00A0Then switch back to the ship and do the same. Repeat\u00A0to get the desired accuracy. Doing this, you don\u0027t even need \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E to dock successfully.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s a bug where if your docking port isn\u0027t aligned with the center-of-mass, automatic alignment via \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E won\u0027t work quite right, but the nav-ball still seems to be correct.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"putnamto","CreatedById":184648,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-02T01:26:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nalso turn off \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E on the docking ship when you are very close or else \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E can really screw it up\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snark","CreatedById":125662,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-02T01:59:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223514672\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181040\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221546388889\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022193139\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022WillWam\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, WillWam said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease consider reposting that on the current forum software!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWould love to, except that unlike the old software, \u0022blog entry\u0022 isn\u0027t a thing on the new software.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"putnamto","CreatedById":184648,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-02T02:16:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223514701\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181040\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221546394362\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022125662\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Snark\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, Snark said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWould love to, except that unlike the old software, \u0022blog entry\u0022 isn\u0027t a thing on the new software.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhere do you get the red prograde marker? ive never had such a thing\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"WillWam","CreatedById":193139,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-02T02:32:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223514706\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181040\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221546395375\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184648\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022putnamto\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, putnamto said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhere do you get the red prograde marker? ive never had such a thing\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s a docking alignment mod\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snark","CreatedById":125662,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-02T02:34:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223514706\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181040\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221546395375\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184648\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022putnamto\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, putnamto said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhere do you get the red prograde marker? ive never had such a thing\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom a mod:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4350650926\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/152739-14-navball-docking-alignment-indicator-community-edition-v2/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:228px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:10px;\u0022\u003E(It\u0027s discussed in the blog entry that I link to above.)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}